tafsir[9]{c,v,t}:
  85,2,"He took an oath by the day of judgment in which He promised to gather all creation."
  85,4,"Those who made a huge crevice in the ground are cursed."
  85,5,"In which they lit a fire and threw the believers into it alive."
  85,6,"While they sat around that crevice filled with fire."
  85,9,"The One to Whom alone belongs control of the heavens and control of the earth. He is aware of everything. No affair of His servants is hidden from Him."
  85,13,"He begins the creation and the punishment and repeats them."
  85,14,"He is Forgiving of the sins of His servants who repent and He loves His allies who are Mindful."
  85,15,"Possessor of the Noble Throne."
  85,20,"Allah surrounds and keeps a record of their actions. Nothing of that misses him and He will give them the recompense for the same."